50|$|Deliberative {{assemblies}} - {{bodies that}} use parliamentary procedure {{to arrive at}} decisions - use several <b>methods</b> <b>of</b> <b>voting</b> on motions (formal proposal by a member or members of a deliberative assembly that the assembly take certain action). The regular <b>methods</b> <b>of</b> <b>voting</b> in such bodies are a voice vote, a rising vote, and a show of hands. Additional forms of voting include a recorded vote and balloting. The assembly could decide on the voting method by adopting a motion on it. Legislatures may have their own voting methods.|$|E
