5000|$|A simple rising vote (in {{which the}} number <b>of</b> members <b>voting</b> {{on each side}} stand, or [...] "rise") is used principally in {{cases in which the}} chair {{believes}} a voice vote has been taken with an inconclusive result, or upon a motion to divide the assembly. A rising vote is also the normal <b>method</b> <b>of</b> <b>voting</b> on motions requiring a two-thirds vote for adoption. It can also be used as the first <b>method</b> <b>of</b> <b>voting</b> when only a majority vote is required if the chair believes in advance that a voice vote will be inconclusive. The chair can also order the rising vote to be counted.|$|R
